4 C. 1. The State Department of Education shall create the
5 designated Internet website for publication described in subsection
6 B of this section no later than ninety (90) days after the effective
7 date of this act.
8 2. The State Department of Education shall include hyperlinks
9 on the Internet website, in a conspicuous manner, that provide
10 access to the guidance documents received pursuant to subsection B
11 of this section.
12 D. If a guidance document is rescinded by the United States
13 Department of Education, the State Department of Education shall
14 maintain the rescinded guidance document at the location described
15 in subsection C of this section and indicate within fifteen (15)
16 days of such rescission:
17 1. That the document has been rescinded; and
18 2. The date the document was rescinded.
19 E. For purposes of this section, "guidance document" means a
20 federal agency statement of general applicability, other than a rule
21 that has the force and effect of law promulgated in accordance with
22 the notice and comment procedures under 5 U.S.C., Section 553, that
23 is designated by an agency official as setting forth a policy or
24 interpretation on a statutory, regulatory, or technical issue. A
